<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>WordCraft | CBSE Class 11 & 12 English + CUET English Prep</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,400;9..144,600;9..144,700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --indigo: #1E2A4A;
    --indigo-light: #2D3D63;
    --amber: #F5A623;
    --bg: #FAF8F4;
    --slate: #5C6478;
    --coral: #E8634C;
    --plum: #6B4E9E;
    --border: #E5E1D8;
  }
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
  body { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; background: var(--bg); color: var(--indigo); line-height: 1.6; }
  h1, h2, h3 { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; }
  .label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  header { background: var(--indigo); color: var(--bg); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }
  .nav-wrap { max-width: 1140px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .logo { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--bg); text-decoration: none; }
  .logo span { color: var(--amber); }
  .hero { max-width: 1140px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem); font-weight: 700; max-width: 16ch; line-height: 1.15; }
  .hero p { color: var(--slate); max-width: 56ch; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .lens-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .lens-col h2 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .tile-stack { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .subject-tile { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem; text-decoration: none; color: var(--indigo); display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .subject-tile h3 { font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .subject-tile p { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--slate); }
  .lens-col.exam .subject-tile { border-left: 4px solid var(--coral); }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .lens-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  footer { background: var(--indigo); color: rgba(250,248,244,0.6); padding: 2rem 1.5rem; text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <div class="nav-wrap">
    <a href="/" class="logo">Word<span>Craft</span></a>
  </div>
</header>
<main class="hero">
  <h1>English, taught around how you're actually being tested.</h1>
  <p>Whether you need chapter-wise notes for your board exam or focused practice for CUET English after Class 12 — start from your class, or start from your exam.</p>

  <div class="lens-grid">
    <div class="lens-col">
      <h2 class="label">By Class — Curriculum</h2>
      <div class="tile-stack">
        <a href="/english-notes/portrait-of-a-lady" class="subject-tile">
          <div>
            <h3>The Portrait of a Lady</h3>
            <p>Class 11 — Prose chapter notes</p>
          </div>
          <span>→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="lens-col exam">
      <h2 class="label">By Exam — Goal-based</h2>
      <div class="tile-stack">
        <a href="#" class="subject-tile">
          <div>
            <h3>CUET English</h3>
            <p>Coming soon</p>
          </div>
          <span>→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>
<footer>WordCraft — English for Class 11, 12 & CUET</footer>
</body>
</html>